Elgeyo Marakwet Governor Alex Tolgos says he is ready to square out with his rivals during the jubilee nominations and he asked aspirants in Jubilee not to flee from the party over fears of unfair nominations ahead of the August 8th polls.Tolgos says the aspirants should feel safe in jubilee because everything possible will be done to ensure the nominations are free and fair to satisfy both candidates and members of the party.&ldquo;Some aspirants in Jubilee have been living in fear and planning to relocate to other parties because they fear the nominations will be unfair. Do away with that feeling and remain in the party", said Tolgos.